                        "name": "9.C.4 Share of the length of electified operated railway lines in total length of operated railway lines",
                      
                        "goal": "Goal 9. Industry, innovation and infrastructure",
                      
                        "priority": "Strengthening the availability of transport infrastructure and the coherence of public communication in the region",
                      
                        "definition": "The basis for calculating the indicator is the total length of electrified railway lines in operation on 31 December.",
                      
                        "unit": "percent",
                      
                        "dimensions": "total",
                      
                        "methodology": "A railway line is an element of the railway network between two junction (or terminal) stations.The length of railway lines in operation is the sum of the construction lengths of standard gauge, narrow gauge and broad gauge railway lines. The construction length of railway lines is understood as the distance between their terminal points measured on single-track lines - along the track axis, and on multi-track lines - along the axis of the longest track.",
                      
